# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules (Next.js static export copies public/ to out/).
# Syntax: /from /to STATUS. 301 = permanent (transfers SEO link equity).
# v2026-04-20a — added 404-catch-all rules for non-indexed slugs.
#
# SEO aliases — users Google "AAPL stock" far more than "AAPL signal", so
# /stock/* 301s to the canonical /signal/* page. No duplicate-content penalty,
# Google transfers all PageRank to the canonical URL, and we capture the higher-
# volume search intent.

/stock/:ticker     /signal/:ticker/    301
/stock/:ticker/    /signal/:ticker/    301
/stocks/:ticker    /signal/:ticker/    301
/stocks/:ticker/   /signal/:ticker/    301

# Common plural confusion
/investors/:slug   /investor/:slug/    301
/investors/:slug/  /investor/:slug/    301

# Common typos & alternate paths
/stock             /ticker/            301
/stocks            /ticker/            301
/stock/            /ticker/            301
/stocks/           /ticker/            301

# 404 RECOVERY removed 2026-04-20 — the catch-all `/section/:slug 302`
# pattern was over-matching real static-file paths in CF Pages, breaking
# production. CF Pages did NOT serve `out/ticker/AAPL/index.html` first
# as the docs implied. The right fix is per-page conditional rendering of
# cross-links (only link to `/ticker/X/` when X is in TICKER_INDEX) — see
# components/{Activist,ShortInterest,Congress}Summary.tsx for the pattern.
# That route prevents 404s at the source instead of papering over them.
